The paper deals with the problem of trace reconstruction, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and involves the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem also involves the recovery of a population of strings from traces, which is related to the field of data mining (cs.DM). The paper also uses techniques from machine learning and probability theory, which are relevant to the fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
